In reality, everyone is dancing around the real issue.  <br>
<br>
The issue is Death Sucks.  Period.    To do advance, you WILL die, and likely Die a Lot.   Death, even with 96% means you will eventually have to XP grind.  <br>
<br>
The simple solution at this point is a combination of things:<br>
<br>
1) XP loss to Death at lvl 60 is Bogus.  flat out.   At MOST, an unrezzed death should be 2.5 blues MAX, preferably 1.5 blues.<br>
<br>
2) There needs to be another Dropped source of Rez Sticks.   The vox stick for 10 charge 90% is a decent start.   There needs to be another one.   Say 30 second recast, High level mob to drop it, 90% rez on it, unlimited save for time.   Required level to use it 50.   (I think the Cleric Epic should be 55, but that is water under the bridge)<br>
<br>
With this combination you achieve a sort of balance.   yes, it is GREAT to have a cleric (or 2 or 3) with the epic, but it is not a MUST have for the guild.<br>
<br>
You get the cleric is 90% rez stick.   Wipe out of 30 people, but that cleric was camped, or is rezed back By a FD monk/Sk.<br>
<br>
Start Rezing.  It will take 15 minutes to rez everyone 90%.  everyone lost 2.5 blues to death, post rez, everyone lost 0.25% of a blue.  yes, there is a loss there.   however, you can taked 20 90% rez deaths before you lose a full orange in lvl 60.   You get 50-80 (average person in 60) before you would drop back into 59.   Even on a 5 day a week raid guild, you should be able to maintain that type of Death rate.   <br>
<br>
Then, if you DO get the 96% epic, GREAT!   Now the Death/REZ xp loss is essentially negligable.  yeah, it is there, but you can die a LOT more, Experiment a LOT more, and not worry so much.<br>
<br>
The ONE flaw with this method is the 90% rez stick would still HURT, and hurt BAD if you are not lvl 60.   All the other levels you lose a lot of time without the 6%, especially since I am advocating a change to xp loss for lvl 60 only.  <br>
<br>
Doing this though, would allow MORE Click Sticks to get into the game.  It would provide more convenience, less overall fear, with the same rate of XP loss today.   However, the same rate means there is still REASON to get the cleric epic, but it does not make it a MUST have item.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 copper.  Take it for what it is worth.....but anyway you look at it, death xp loss at 60 is absurd.<br>
