<br>
And, I think lowering the effect to a 90% rez is a great idea. Most epics (all but cleric?) are no longer as powerful as classes *best* weapon or spell. Why should a cleric's epic effect be equal to their best rez? (ignoring the once per 3 day 100% rez/ no rez effects AA skill). However, it was very plainly stated by the developers at FF that SOE has no intention of changing ANY aspect of the 'old' epics at this point... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/4/02 9:20:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=124.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something for everyone concerned about ragefire</span><hr size=1> What I don't understand about this arguement...  <br>
<br>
Clerics can already cast 96% rez. The epic being able to do that faster, without mana, is probably one hell of a convenience. So the ONLY thing that lowering the value of the epic rez to say 75% does is change the time for a raid recovery.<br>
<br>
If the time it takes to recover without 75% rez is greater than the time it takes to earn back the difference in XP, people WILL still want the 75% rez. If you must have a 96% rez, then wait until the Cleric has the mana. If getting back into the fight immediately is more important, then eat the XP difference.<br>
<br>
Correct me if I am wrong, but the Paladin's highest Rez (90%) is less than is currently offered by an inanimate object (96%). Reducing the rez of the Cleric epic to 75% should not only reduce the *must have* of the epic and stop the squabbling, but it will also increase the value of a Paladin's raid abilities.  <br>
<br>
And I think everyone will agree, increasing the Paladin's value should be Verant's primary focus from day one until the time I retire. :) <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>
